T1  - Measurement errors and bounded OLS estimates
AU  - Levi, Maurice D.
JO  - Journal of Econometrics
VL  - 6
IS  - 2
SP  - 165
EP  - 171
PY  - 1977
DA  - 1977/09/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(77)90013-6
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407677900136
AB  - In a multiple linear regression model with one mismeasured independent variable, all coefficients are asymptotically biased. It is shown how in OLS, an examination of the sign of the cofactors of the variance-covariance matrix of measured values can be used to obtain large sample bounds on the coefficients. The method involves forward regression and regression on the mismeasured variable. Bounds are generally obtained on the coefficient of the mismeasured variable and often obtained on the remaining coefficients with no knowledge of the size of the measurement error.
