UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407677900124
AB  - A multiple equation model of the seemingly unrelated regressions type is considered. We derive an Edgeworth expansion up to 0(T-1), where T is the sample size, of the finite sampls distribution function of the seemingly unrelated regression estimator of the parameters in thie model. We examine the two-equation case where our results can be related to exact theory in the special case of orthogonal exogenous variables and we take as a particular numerical example Zellner's original application to micro-investment functions.
